cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of logic programming systems through the use of or-parallelism and tabling. As such, it is most likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. However, it also involves parallel computing (cs.DC), logic in computer science (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) to some extent.
